    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks for that. So, looking at those two perspectives, it seems like a pretty intense debate between judicial power and democratic will. In your view, does the argument for protecting 'inherent liberties' via substantive due process carry more weight when compared to the concerns about originalism and judicial overreach? Like, is one side's logic fundamentally stronger?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
